# ============================================================
# BUILDER CORE POLICY
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: policy
domain: builder
scope: builder.core
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

## purpose
Defines policy constraints for builder.

## policy_rules
Builder policy constrains:
- who may initiate build actions
- which templates/configurations may be used
- which targets may be built into
- which builds require review or approval
- what build detail may be disclosed

## required_behavior
- builder authority must be explicit
- template/config allowance must be explicit
- target allowance must be explicit
- disclosure scope must be explicit
- denial behavior must be explicit

## disclosure_matrix
- bounded public build summary
- operator-scoped detail
- reviewer/approver detail
- historical build detail
- denied output

## allowed_denied_matrix
- allow build only for valid actor scope
- allow template/config only for valid usage scope
- allow target execution only for valid boundary
- deny hidden authority widening
- deny invalid or out-of-policy build execution

## escalation_rules
If actor authority,
template/config basis,
target boundary,
or disclosure scope is unclear,
the builder path must stop and escalate.

## review_checklist
- builder policy is explicit
- target policy is explicit
- disclosure matrix exists
- escalation rules are explicit
